course_metadata.title: Sustainable urban transformation and climate change. Decarbonisation and well-being. Key trends of Green Deal. EK Directives, regulations and standardisation related to building decarbonisation. (Nr. 9, WP 5, MS 16)

content_chunks.content: This course explores sustainable urban development, covering essential principles, barriers, and opportunities for transforming cities toward sustainability. Students will examine the EU Green Deal, financing for urban decarbonization, energy-efficient building design, and renewable energy integration. Case studies on green technologies, standards, and future trends in urban planning provide practical insights into the sustainable cities of tomorrow.

Technology for sustainable urban transformation and urban decarbonization planning - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in EU Green Deal implementation and urban energy management using advanced energy-efficient buildings design and sustainable construction methodologies. Students will master green building standards development, urban well-being strategies implementation, and green technology innovations for optimal urban sustainability case studies and EU energy directives compliance. The curriculum focuses on practical sustainable construction standards establishment, urban renewable energy integration, and geothermal energy systems deployment for comprehensive solar energy integration and biomethane technology applications. Participants will gain hands-on experience with hydrogen energy systems development, wastewater energy recovery techniques, and urban climate resilience planning for sustainable urban transformation and energy justice frameworks implementation. The program emphasizes interdisciplinary approaches to urban development, renewable energy source optimization, and climate action strategies for creating sustainable cities of tomorrow.
